## Who can log in and what do they see?

There are **two completely separate worlds** of users in this system.

**World 1: The company staff (tenant-scoped users)**
These are people *inside* Zenith Logistics, Dangote, or whatever company is using the app. They log in and see *only their company's data*. Within their company, they have different roles:

- **HR Manager** — can add/edit employees, update salaries, manage records
- **Payroll Manager** — can run and review payroll calculations
- **Finance Director** — can approve and authorize payments
- **Regular Employee** — can only see their own payslips and personal info

Nobody at Dangote can see Zenith's data. Nobody at Zenith can see Dangote's. Same app, different sealed universes.

**World 2: The platform owner (super admin)**
This is whoever built and sells the software. They have a god-mode dashboard where they can create new company accounts (onboard a new tenant), manage subscriptions, handle support issues. They never touch payroll data — they just manage which companies exist on the platform.

**Who sets the roles?** When a company first signs up, the platform owner creates their account and assigns one person as the company's **Super Admin** (usually the IT lead or Head of HR). That Super Admin then logs in and creates all other users — assigns Amaka as HR Manager, Emeka as Payroll Manager, Mrs. Okonkwo as Finance Director. They can also deactivate users who leave the company. So role assignment flows downward: platform owner → company super admin → everyone else.

**Can regular employees log in?** Yes, but to a very stripped-down view — basically just "my payslips" and "my personal details." Some companies enable this, some don't. It's a permission toggle the company super admin controls.

