## Pulling it all together — the full picture of who does what

Let me map every actor to their actions cleanly:

| Who | What they do in the app |
|---|---|
| **Platform Super Admin** | Creates company accounts, manages subscriptions |
| **Company Super Admin** | Creates users, assigns roles, configures company settings, links bank details |
| **HR Manager** | Adds/edits employees, manages salaries, assignments, org structure |
| **Payroll Manager** | Runs payroll calculations, reviews results, flags issues, submits for approval |
| **Finance Director** | Reviews final register, approves payroll, downloads payment file for the bank |
| **Finance Team** | Takes payment file to corporate banking portal, uploads it, confirms transfers |
| **Employee** | Views own payslips, updates personal/bank details |

Notice the Finance Team step — that's a human action *outside the app* (for Model A). The app's job ends at generating the file. The human carries it to the bank.

