## The one thing to nail before any of this

The thing the PRD is most serious about — and which will make or break everything else — is **who can do what, enforced in code, not just in the UI**. 

Emeka should not be able to approve his own payroll even if he finds the API endpoint. Mrs. Okonkwo should not be able to edit Chidi's salary. These rules live in the backend and get checked on every single request. The frontend just *reflects* the rules by hiding buttons — but the backend *enforces* them by rejecting unauthorized requests. That's the RBAC system the PRD keeps mentioning.

