## The shared flows that cut across everyone

**Forgot password** — same on every role. They click "Forgot password" on the login screen, enter their email, receive a reset link (token-based, expires in 1 hour), click it, set a new password, get redirected to login. Exactly like **Cowrywise** or any Nigerian fintech app's reset flow.

**Session expiry** — after say 30 minutes of inactivity, their session expires. Next time they click anything, the app quietly redirects them to login. When they log back in, they land back where they were trying to go. Like how **GTBank mobile** kicks you out after idle time.

**Two-Factor Authentication** — for Finance Director and Super Admin roles especially, after entering password they get an OTP to their phone (SMS) or email. They enter the OTP. Then they're in. Like how **Paystack dashboard** requires 2FA for high-permission accounts. This is a financial app — the Finance Director approving ₦24.3M transfers should definitely have a second factor.

